Tesla is setting itself up well to be very successful in two massive future markets: Autonomy and robotics.

Tesla's new $16.5 billion (likely much higher ultimately) chip deal with Samsung is some evidence of that. While Tesla will take part in shaping the future, companies like Ford and GM seem like they will get left behind as they find it hard to pivot into this new world of AI, autonomy and robotics.
